Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.23,0:00:04.31,Default,,0,0,0,,What in the world is that Servant?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.31,0:00:08.36,Default,,0,0,0,,She's Iskandar's primary confidante.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.61,0:00:10.32,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why I'm troubled.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.36,0:00:17.99,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't recall seeing her among those in Ionioi Hetairoi.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.87,0:00:20.70,Default,,0,0,0,,One who accompanied the King of Conquerors,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.70,0:00:22.54,Default,,0,0,0,,a comrade in arms who shared his dream,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.16,0:00:27.00,Default,,0,0,0,,should be fighting alongside him after death as a Heroic Spirit.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.50,0:00:29.38,Default,,0,0,0,,And yet...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.96,0:00:32.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Waver!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.17,0:00:34.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Welcome back!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.30,0:00:40.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Just as you asked, I arranged for the auction to be delayed!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.60,0:00:44.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Imperfections in the catalog, delays in the train...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.19,0:00:47.77,Default,,0,0,0,,He attacked from every front. He was on a rampage.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.77,0:00:52.69,Default,,0,0,0,,As I needed to add extra funding, I wrung in a deal to delay the auction as much as possible!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.69,0:00:54.15,Default,,0,0,0,,A habitual complainer...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.40,0:00:57.53,Default,,0,0,0,,They said they would push the start to midnight tonight.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.33,0:01:01.29,Default,,0,0,0,,So, half a day left.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.12,0:01:07.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. Shishigou's report is just like what I had Gray tell you.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.50,0:01:09.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh no, thank you for the hard work.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.38,0:01:14.17,Default,,0,0,0,,You may be recovering from illness, but I do anticipate your active role in the situation.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.88,0:01:16.93,Default,,0,0,0,,You're wondering if I'm enjoying this?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.93,0:01:18.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course I am!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.00,0:01:27.00,Default,chptr,0,0,0,,{OP}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.41,0:02:56.45,Default,chptr,0,0,0,,{Episode}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.40,0:03:01.41,Default,,0,0,0,,We've already decided that Karabo was the perpetrator, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.82,0:03:03.70,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not set in stone yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.12,0:03:05.12,Default,,0,0,0,,And...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.58,0:03:08.87,Default,,0,0,0,,the perpetrator for this case is clearly my enemy.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.25,0:03:11.08,Default,,0,0,0,,The perpetrator for this case?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.08,0:03:13.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you mean the one who killed Trisha?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.54,0:03:16.55,Default,,0,0,0,,The one who stole the relic from you?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.80,0:03:19.01,Default,,0,0,0,,The Master of that Heroic Spirit?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.01,0:03:21.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Without a doubt, all three are the same person.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.26,0:03:26.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I would like to ask you for help once again.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.68,0:03:33.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, why do I have to do something like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.90,0:03:36.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I hate all of you!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.32,0:03:41.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I hate people who look like they were recognized for their efforts!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.11,0:03:45.41,Default,,0,0,0,,I hate self-conclusive people who think they don't have to be recognized by others!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.03,0:03:49.75,Default,,0,0,0,,You look like you fit into both of those categories!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.00,0:03:51.96,Default,,0,0,0,,You're the worst of the worst! I detest you!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.96,0:03:53.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Master isn't saying that—
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.46,0:03:54.71,Default,,0,0,0,,What he does is no different!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.00,0:03:57.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Because you guys are trying to stand up against her!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.13,0:04:01.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Looking at that makes me feel miserable!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.13,0:04:03.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Miss Olga Marie...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.38,0:04:05.34,Default,,0,0,0,,You guys are up against Policies!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.89,0:04:09.68,Default,,0,0,0,,They only think of all of us as pawns!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.81,0:04:12.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I know that.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.14,0:04:15.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Even then, with what's behind all that,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.06,0:04:18.07,Default,,0,0,0,,I will fight!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.40,0:04:24.41,Default,,0,0,0,,I hate more than anything how I can't completely reject you guys and your ways.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.11,0:04:27.07,Default,,0,0,0,,You are courageous.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.50,0:04:33.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Let me tell you an old story.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.55,0:04:42.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I stole that relic.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.84,0:04:47.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead of training to build my pathetic self up to confront my mentor,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.14,0:04:50.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I had the misconception that I could have him recognize me with stolen powers.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.56,0:04:56.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't have courage, like you do now,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.69,0:05:01.32,Default,,0,0,0,,to throw my own feelings at the face of an adult.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.57,0:05:06.41,Default,,0,0,0,,I am simply a survivor.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.87,0:05:09.70,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not like I'm standing up against anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.20,0:05:13.58,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just harder for me to stay crouching.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.33,0:05:15.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Master...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.17,0:05:17.58,Default,,0,0,0,,This time,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.08,0:05:20.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to win for sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.84,0:05:25.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Because the perpetrator for this case ended up being my enemy,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.01,0:05:28.43,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't lose against him at any cost!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.93,0:05:31.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't you want to win, Olga Marie?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.56,0:05:35.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't you want to prove to the world
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.85,0:05:38.65,Default,,0,0,0,,that you won't simply cry yourself to sleep
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.65,0:05:41.48,Default,,0,0,0,,when someone murders your attendant?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.15,0:05:45.07,Default,,0,0,0,,You just called me "Olga Marie."
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.07,0:05:48.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Not as "Animusphere" or "the Lord's daughter."
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.66,0:05:51.16,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right. I need you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.74,0:05:57.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't forget, Lord El-Melloi II, this is a deal.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.63,0:06:01.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I can feel the exhaust shaking my stomach!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.25,0:06:05.97,Default,,0,0,0,,American cars really are great!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.97,0:06:11.93,Default,,0,0,0,,More like, were you really sent here by Reines, Mr. Shishigou?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.18,0:06:17.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, that's right! Can you finally tell us why you pulled us out of our special lecture?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.06,0:06:21.61,Default,,0,0,0,,A moving car is a boundary between the living world and the underworld.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.98,0:06:24.94,Default,,0,0,0,,It creates a pseudo-enclosed space both physically and spiritually.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.48,0:06:27.07,Default,,0,0,0,,It should be okay now.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.49,0:06:31.07,Default,,0,0,0,,That is your new assignment.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.24,0:06:35.87,Default,,0,0,0,,I see. This truly is...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.16,0:06:39.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. This job is suited for us, Flatt!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.34,0:06:46.38,Default,,0,0,0,,The Greater Grail of Fuyuki is useless?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.38,0:06:47.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.88,0:06:49.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Dad had said that in the past.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.38,0:06:52.60,Default,,0,0,0,,As far as I am aware,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.60,0:06:55.64,Default,,0,0,0,,that Greater Grail is genuine no matter how you think about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.02,0:06:57.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Otherwise,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.64,0:06:59.69,Default,,0,0,0,,it wouldn't be able to summon Heroic Spirits.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.69,0:07:01.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Like I would know.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.15,0:07:05.36,Default,,0,0,0,,That was my dad's conclusions for calling off going to the Holy Grail War.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.36,0:07:08.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Trisha was looking into the Holy Grail War. It was because...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.11,0:07:15.58,Default,,0,0,0,,she wanted to know why your father stopped loving you.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.08,0:07:17.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Trisha did?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.75,0:07:21.17,Default,,0,0,0,,And chasing after your father's source of information,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.42,0:07:23.42,Default,,0,0,0,,she was murdered.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.59,0:07:29.42,Default,,0,0,0,,It seems like illusions.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.09,0:07:31.97,Default,,0,0,0,,You mean the Holy Grail War?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.64,0:07:34.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.39,0:07:36.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Your Holy Grail War,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.89,0:07:38.72,Default,,0,0,0,,the Child of Ainnash,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.97,0:07:42.31,Default,,0,0,0,,this Mystic Eyes Collection Train,\Nmemories of Trisha...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.77,0:07:45.82,Default,,0,0,0,,They all feel like scenery left behind.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.77,0:07:49.78,Default,,0,0,0,,The host has long since gone walking yonder,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.03,0:07:53.32,Default,,0,0,0,,but the shadow is still left behind in present time.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.91,0:07:56.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Why is everyone desperately holding on,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.28,0:08:00.83,Default,,0,0,0,,knowing that there's only the shadow left?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.79,0:08:03.54,Default,,0,0,0,,It's like an afterimage.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.71,0:08:07.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, that's it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.92,0:08:08.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Master?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.51,0:08:12.51,Default,,0,0,0,,You are truly the heir of Animusphere.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.76,0:08:15.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Do those eyes have a birds-eye view of the world?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.60,0:08:19.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Wh-What? Don't compliment me all of a sudden!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.27,0:08:23.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh no, you're worthy of praise as an individual.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.44,0:08:27.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I need to contact someone.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.73,0:08:28.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll be right back.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.94,0:08:34.28,Default,,0,0,0,,This is Luviagelita. Who is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.28,0:08:35.41,Default,,0,0,0,,It's me.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.41,0:08:38.45,Default,,0,0,0,,I heard you've been assisting Reines.\NI give my thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.87,0:08:41.95,Default,,0,0,0,,It is all fine as I've been remunerated.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.20,0:08:43.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Or is this an additional request?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.08,0:08:48.79,Default,,0,0,0,,It is. How did Lord Animusphere get to know of the Holy Grail War?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.21,0:08:50.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Even in the Clock Tower,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.75,0:08:54.01,Default,,0,0,0,,a surprisingly few magi even noticed that event.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.01,0:08:57.68,Default,,0,0,0,,There are traces of someone controlling the information.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.01,0:09:03.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Looking at how Adashino has been reacting, I don't think it was Policies. However,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.68,0:09:07.19,Default,,0,0,0,,there's no doubt that someone got Animusphere moving.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.48,0:09:11.19,Default,,0,0,0,,And Trisha was investigating it when she was killed.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.57,0:09:13.57,Default,,0,0,0,,You may have forgotten,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.82,0:09:17.07,Default,,0,0,0,,but I'm not a member of the El-Melloi Classroom.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.07,0:09:20.99,Default,,0,0,0,,I've simply hired you as a personal tutor.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.74,0:09:26.62,Default,,0,0,0,,When the Holy Grail War is over, I promise to give you personal lectures.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.87,0:09:29.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll make sure to wring out all your secrets when you do.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.21,0:09:38.09,Default,,0,0,0,,For us, the Edelfelt family, to intervene in conflict to make the greatest profit...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.39,0:09:41.01,Default,,0,0,0,,It's finally time to show what we can really do!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.94,0:09:48.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Bright.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.77,0:09:52.82,Default,,0,0,0,,This is an artificial environmental model created by Animusphere.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.11,0:09:54.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Is this enough?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.28,0:09:55.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.40,0:09:58.53,Default,,0,0,0,,With a leyline map this accurate.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.49,0:10:04.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I see. I get it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.33,0:10:08.12,Default,,0,0,0,,It's only a matter of what order.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.75,0:10:11.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I finally caught you this time!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.42,0:10:15.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Why didn't I notice this?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.46,0:10:17.84,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a not a mystery at all!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.22,0:10:22.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Why Hephaestion was female or why she wasn't in Ionioi Hetairoi are not the issues!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.89,0:10:24.60,Default,,0,0,0,,The question is...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.97,0:10:28.85,Default,,0,0,0,,why did that thing claim to be Hephaestion?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.85,0:10:30.35,Default,,0,0,0,,The whydunit.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.35,0:10:32.11,Default,,0,0,0,,This is no true case.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.36,0:10:35.19,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the afterimage of what was once a case.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.19,0:10:38.86,Default,,0,0,0,,No, it's a remnant that sees even less salvation than that.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.07,0:10:41.12,Default,,0,0,0,,What in the world are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.66,0:10:44.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, the final part.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.37,0:10:46.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Miss Adashino had been hiding it,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.37,0:10:48.50,Default,,0,0,0,,but other than Trisha Fellows' severed head,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.50,0:10:52.25,Default,,0,0,0,,wasn't there something else hidden within the imaginary space?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.47,0:11:04.89,Default,,0,0,0,,This fell out along with Trisha's head.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.14,0:11:07.14,Default,,0,0,0,,This is what I saw!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.52,0:11:09.89,Default,,0,0,0,,As expected. Damn Adashino!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.06,0:11:13.40,Default,,0,0,0,,She removed it from her deduction as the puzzle pieces wouldn't fit with this.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.69,0:11:16.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Will that become the key to reaching the true perpetrator?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.11,0:11:18.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.57,0:11:23.24,Default,,0,0,0,,The deductions made by Policies will completely be overturned.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.54,0:11:36.05,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}Everyone, we will begin the Mystic Eyes Auction shortly.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.46,0:11:43.05,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}Please head over to the Warehouse for a Myriad of Mystic Eyeballs, the Pandemonium.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.48,0:11:50.85,Default,,0,0,0,,25 million dollars.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.85,0:11:51.94,Default,,0,0,0,,30 million dollars.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.94,0:11:53.44,Default,,0,0,0,,40 million dollars!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.77,0:11:58.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Sold for 40 million dollars.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.03,0:12:03.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing less from an authority on Mystic Eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.16,0:12:06.62,Default,,0,0,0,,She doesn't hold back for notable Mystic Eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.62,0:12:07.99,Default,,0,0,0,,And lastly,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.33,0:12:10.16,Default,,0,0,0,,our main item for this auction!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.33,0:12:15.17,Default,,0,0,0,,These are the Jewel-class Mystic Eyes of Transience.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.05,0:12:20.42,Default,,0,0,0,,We will start at 30 million dollars.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.76,0:12:22.88,Default,,0,0,0,,40 million.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.90,0:12:23.56,Default,,0,0,0,,50 million!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.76,0:12:24.57,Default,,0,0,0,,70 million!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.57,0:12:25.30,Default,,0,0,0,,80 million!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.51,0:12:26.35,Default,,0,0,0,,90 million!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.51,0:12:27.35,Default,,0,0,0,,100 million!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.22,0:12:30.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Even a Picasso piece is worth that much.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.89,0:12:34.65,Default,,0,0,0,,If it's Jewel-class Mystic Eyes, it won't end at this level.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.94,0:12:36.31,Default,,0,0,0,,130 million.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.31,0:12:39.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh no, no, no! Policies has to be joking about this!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.86,0:12:41.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm serious of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.32,0:12:43.78,Default,,0,0,0,,140 million.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.78,0:12:45.16,Default,,0,0,0,,150 million.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.36,0:12:46.57,Default,,0,0,0,,160 million.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.03,0:12:50.24,Default,,0,0,0,,200 million!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.33,0:12:53.83,Default,,0,0,0,,230 million.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.46,0:12:57.84,Default,,0,0,0,,230 million. Going once!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.51,0:13:02.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Going twice!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.17,0:13:04.97,Default,,0,0,0,,240 million!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.26,0:13:08.22,Default,,0,0,0,,What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.60,0:13:10.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I said, "240 million dollars."
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.22,0:13:12.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Auctioneer,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.47,0:13:15.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I would like you to please keep going.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.61,0:13:18.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Well then...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.40,0:13:20.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Hold on!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.52,0:13:22.74,Default,,0,0,0,,This is heating up way too much!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.99,0:13:25.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Auctioneer, let us take a break!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.66,0:13:28.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Motion accepted.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.20,0:13:33.58,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the meaning of this, Waver?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.25,0:13:39.54,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't possibly get that much money ready in your current state!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.09,0:13:43.63,Default,,0,0,0,,But you were about to stand down at 230 million!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.05,0:13:46.43,Default,,0,0,0,,All things considered...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.68,0:13:50.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Though, that said, I'm dubious of Yvette's wallet, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.43,0:13:53.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, how much can Policies spend?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.43,0:13:55.64,Default,,0,0,0,,They don't care how much they spend.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.73,0:14:00.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Those Mystic Eyes are under Policies' management now.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.52,0:14:05.61,Default,,0,0,0,,The money from the successful bid isn't going to Karabo but to Policies.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.61,0:14:09.78,Default,,0,0,0,,They can pay hundreds of millions of dollars,\Nand it all goes back to them?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.78,0:14:13.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, there are limits to how much money Adashino can move at her discretion,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.16,0:14:17.50,Default,,0,0,0,,and some money will be taken as commission so it won't make a clear profit.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.00,0:14:20.25,Default,,0,0,0,,But it's a shrewd plan suited to her nature.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.58,0:14:24.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And what are you after, Waver?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.26,0:14:27.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Will you seriously go against how much funding Policies has?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.05,0:14:31.14,Default,,0,0,0,,The enemy probably didn't expect the prices to go this high.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.39,0:14:34.31,Default,,0,0,0,,He surely has to be concentrating during the auction.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.31,0:14:37.02,Default,,0,0,0,,That's when I'll ready my trump card.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.35,0:14:40.10,Default,,0,0,0,,This is quite an expensive diversion you've got here!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.10,0:14:42.61,Default,,0,0,0,,You could buy a stealth fighter with it!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.28,0:14:46.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Waver,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.49,0:14:49.03,Default,,0,0,0,,let me ask you again.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.03,0:14:51.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you promise me that this will be amusing?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.24,0:14:55.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Is this an act worthy of putting a friend's financial ruin on the line?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.04,0:14:58.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you swear that it is?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.08,0:15:01.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I promise you it will surely be to your liking.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.96,0:15:04.92,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, then!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.92,0:15:08.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, it's me. Yeah, me.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.76,0:15:12.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Remember the tuning machine you've been wanting? No, I won't sell it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.55,0:15:15.31,Default,,0,0,0,,But if I use it as collateral, how much can you dish out?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.64,0:15:18.77,Default,,0,0,0,,30 million dollars? No, that's not gonna fly!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.77,0:15:21.06,Default,,0,0,0,,You should at least be able to go 70 million!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.11,0:15:24.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I don't have much time,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.73,0:15:27.57,Default,,0,0,0,,so we can compromise, and I'll settle for 50 million.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.82,0:15:29.32,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll go with that.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.15,0:15:34.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay! You have 130 million extra now!\NWill we be able to fight now?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.45,0:15:39.66,Default,,0,0,0,,By the way, Gray, Reines entrusted you with a card, didn't she?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.91,0:15:42.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, y-yes! This is it!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.13,0:15:45.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't like to add to my debt.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.30,0:15:48.84,Default,,0,0,0,,But with this, I can secure another 30 million.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.84,0:15:52.01,Default,,0,0,0,,What's left is my bank account and hidden fortune.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.38,0:15:54.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, how far can we go?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.68,0:15:57.10,Default,,0,0,0,,This is getting really interesting!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.90,0:16:10.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Why do you go so far?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.03,0:16:11.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Look here.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.15,0:16:17.41,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm a bastard who finds entertainment when others are corrupted or fall from grace.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.95,0:16:25.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I've always been like this, even before I found out I'm physically hindered from becoming a magus.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.50,0:16:28.30,Default,,0,0,0,,However,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.84,0:16:31.67,Default,,0,0,0,,a bastard has dignity of being a bastard.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.92,0:16:33.97,Default,,0,0,0,,If you think it seems fun,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.22,0:16:36.89,Default,,0,0,0,,you need to properly and squarely bet until the ultimate end
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.89,0:16:39.89,Default,,0,0,0,,even if you're betting your parents or your own self!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.14,0:16:44.77,Default,,0,0,0,,If you stay in a safe area without doing so,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.02,0:16:47.77,Default,,0,0,0,,that is no longer a bastard.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.48,0:16:52.28,Default,,0,0,0,,You demote yourself to simply being a cowardly chicken.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.86,0:16:57.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, we will resume from 240 million.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.99,0:16:59.03,Default,,0,0,0,,250 million.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.41,0:17:00.54,Default,,0,0,0,,260 million.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.12,0:17:02.20,Default,,0,0,0,,280 million!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.41,0:17:03.29,Default,,0,0,0,,300 million.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.29,0:17:04.67,Default,,0,0,0,,320 million.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.87,0:17:06.25,Default,,0,0,0,,330 million!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.63,0:17:08.13,Default,,0,0,0,,340 million.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.13,0:17:09.42,Default,,0,0,0,,350 million.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.42,0:17:10.80,Default,,0,0,0,,360 million!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.17,0:17:12.55,Default,,0,0,0,,370 million.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.42,0:17:14.43,Default,,0,0,0,,400 million!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.76,0:17:16.30,Default,,0,0,0,,410 million!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.18,0:17:26.31,Default,,0,0,0,,410 million. Going once!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.23,0:17:30.57,Default,,0,0,0,,420 million.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.98,0:17:32.15,Default,,0,0,0,,430 million!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.94,0:17:34.07,Default,,0,0,0,,460 million!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.61,0:17:35.45,Default,,0,0,0,,500 million!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.21,0:17:47.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Hold on a second!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.50,0:17:49.34,Default,,0,0,0,,We won't allow a second break.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.09,0:17:52.13,Default,,0,0,0,,There is something about Trisha Fellows' death
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.38,0:17:54.51,Default,,0,0,0,,that I want out in the open.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.76,0:17:58.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, what's the matter, Lord El-Melloi II?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.30,0:18:00.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you dissatisfied with my deduction?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.64,0:18:02.68,Default,,0,0,0,,The logic was full of holes,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.68,0:18:04.81,Default,,0,0,0,,but your deduction itself had no errors.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.60,0:18:06.69,Default,,0,0,0,,That is why...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.19,0:18:09.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I would like you to look at this first!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.90,0:18:11.73,Default,,0,0,0,,You know...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.53,0:18:15.07,Default,,0,0,0,,I needed it to resolve the situation.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.49,0:18:17.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I took some liberties to bring it out here.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.49,0:18:21.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's hear the great detective's deductions, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.49,0:18:24.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Then,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.83,0:18:28.75,Default,,0,0,0,,allow me to clear things up, starting with the serial murders from seven years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.46,0:18:33.75,Default,,0,0,0,,In that case, all victims were beheaded, and their heads were missing.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.00,0:18:37.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, what do you think based on the situation?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.64,0:18:41.39,Default,,0,0,0,,That they are dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.64,0:18:42.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.64,0:18:44.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on now, Waver!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.47,0:18:47.23,Default,,0,0,0,,If there's no head, of course they're all dead!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.56,0:18:50.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, what was the reason Trisha Fellows hid her head?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.23,0:18:53.07,Default,,0,0,0,,It was a dying message, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.07,0:18:55.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Yvette Lehmann gets a 3 out of 10.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.61,0:18:57.53,Default,,0,0,0,,She was a wielder of Mystic Eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.53,0:19:01.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Th-Then, the perpetrator tried to take Trisha's Mystic Eyes from her?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.45,0:19:05.87,Default,,0,0,0,,But this train is the only way Mystic Eyes can be extracted from a human corpse.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.16,0:19:08.87,Default,,0,0,0,,No, the victims' heads were all taken.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.12,0:19:10.71,Default,,0,0,0,,They weren't necessarily dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.96,0:19:13.21,Default,,0,0,0,,"You are dead if your head has been taken away."
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.21,0:19:14.96,Default,,0,0,0,,That is in itself an assumption!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.67,0:19:18.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Trisha's head, after being severed,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.38,0:19:19.26,Default,,0,0,0,,was still alive!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.63,0:19:25.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. A talented magus can keep someone alive with just the head.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.01,0:19:29.14,Default,,0,0,0,,That way, he could freely use Mystic Eyes\Nwithout transplanting them.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.60,0:19:32.27,Default,,0,0,0,,You simply need the heads of the Mystic Eye wielders.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.86,0:19:35.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Master, are you saying that the case seven years ago
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.23,0:19:39.03,Default,,0,0,0,,were crimes to seize and use Mystic Eyes at will?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.03,0:19:40.82,Default,,0,0,0,,That's my deduction.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.20,0:19:42.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Then,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.53,0:19:44.16,Default,,0,0,0,,why was Trisha killed?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.66,0:19:47.62,Default,,0,0,0,,She was investigating the case from seven years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.87,0:19:50.46,Default,,0,0,0,,If the perpetrator obtained Mystic Eyes from every victim,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.71,0:19:54.67,Default,,0,0,0,,it should've been possible to obtain information about the Holy Grail War.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.13,0:19:58.55,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why he tried to contact Karabo and myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.96,0:20:01.30,Default,,0,0,0,,In other words, you aren't denying
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.30,0:20:05.43,Default,,0,0,0,,that Karabo Frampton was the perpetrator for the case seven years ago, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.43,0:20:08.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Miss Adashino, are you familiar with this?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.93,0:20:15.56,Default,,0,0,0,,It's what Trisha Fellows hid inside the imaginary spell together with her head.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.27,0:20:19.19,Default,,0,0,0,,As vision is the oldest form of magecraft,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.53,0:20:22.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Mystic Eyes have a myriad of countermeasures.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.11,0:20:26.28,Default,,0,0,0,,For instance, using a lewd talisman to block line of sight of the witness.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.03,0:20:31.54,Default,,0,0,0,,If the power of vision is strong, it can even be reflected.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.58,0:20:34.21,Default,,0,0,0,,A reversal of Mystic Eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.21,0:20:38.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I see. I had foolishly forgotten about that possibility.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.88,0:20:41.97,Default,,0,0,0,,You can manipulate Mystic Eyes that aren't being controlled.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.97,0:20:46.85,Default,,0,0,0,,The reason why you hid this was to prevent everyone from realizing that possibility.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.85,0:20:50.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you want to say that Karabo was being manipulated by Trisha?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.52,0:20:52.56,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a jump in logic.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.56,0:20:57.27,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm saying that the possibility of a third party intervening with Karabo's Mystic Eyes
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.27,0:21:00.99,Default,,0,0,0,,is intentionally lacking from your deduction.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.32,0:21:02.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.03,0:21:04.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Indeed.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.32,0:21:07.41,Default,,0,0,0,,So, the perpetrator and mastermind are separate, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.41,0:21:09.74,Default,,0,0,0,,So, what happens from there?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.12,0:21:13.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Trisha, in her Premonition, predicted that she would meet Karabo.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.96,0:21:19.00,Default,,0,0,0,,She boarded this train to gain the truth about seven years ago from him.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.00,0:21:19.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And then?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.88,0:21:22.51,Default,,0,0,0,,And that was her mistake.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.01,0:21:28.97,Default,,0,0,0,,She lost her life by a blade from the past that could not be prevented by Premonition.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.26,0:21:34.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Um, professor, are you saying that the true perpetrator manipulated Karabo
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.69,0:21:39.19,Default,,0,0,0,,and committed this murder as well as the ones seven years ago?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.23,0:21:46.45,Default,,0,0,0,,There's just one person who can make that possible and also has a motive.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.28,0:21:50.58,Default,,0,0,0,,So, who is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.87,0:21:52.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, that?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.25,0:21:55.12,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the answer.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.02,0:22:10.06,Default,chptr,0,0,0,,{ED}
